02:03.830 --> 02:05.860
I want to wait for Cal and Daddy.

02:05.870 --> 02:06.940
Oh, no, honey.

02:06.950 --> 02:09.800
Let's go home.
We'll get unpacked first.

02:09.820 --> 02:11.780
Honey, you know, I got all kinds
of baseball to catch up on.

02:11.790 --> 02:13.870
He's got his baseball.
I know you miss your brother,

02:13.880 --> 02:15.900
but he'll be here before you know it.

02:15.910 --> 02:18.810
Please, Grandma?

02:18.830 --> 02:20.890
I'm gonna show you something.

02:22.940 --> 02:25.780
All righty, Ollie Bollie.

02:25.790 --> 02:27.960
Flight 828... there.
You see?

02:27.980 --> 02:29.940
It's not gonna arrive
for another few hours.

02:29.950 --> 02:31.820
It's too long to wait.

02:33.800 --> 02:35.830
"See Agent"?
What's that mean?

02:36.890 --> 02:38.870
That's just airline talk, honey.

02:38.880 --> 02:39.960
For passengers on
Montego Air Flight 828,

02:39.970 --> 02:41.880
please see an agent.

02:41.890 --> 02:43.950
- I know it's gonna be bad news.
- Jared, stop.

02:43.960 --> 02:46.790
I should have never proposed
so soon after the accident.

02:46.800 --> 02:47.910
I mean, she's not ready.

02:47.920 --> 02:49.830
Now she's gonna get off that
plane and turn me down.

02:49.840 --> 02:52.880
No. She's gonna get off
that plane and say yes.

02:52.890 --> 02:54.870
- Are you sure?
- Please.

02:54.880 --> 02:56.790
We've been friends since forever.

02:56.800 --> 02:57.970
I'm so totally psychic.

02:58.750 --> 02:59.950
Michaela... am I right?

02:59.960 --> 03:02.800
No, it's Grace.

03:02.810 --> 03:04.800
Hello?

03:05.920 --> 03:07.880
W-What's wrong?

03:07.890 --> 03:09.880
Excuse me.
NYPD, coming through.

03:09.890 --> 03:11.930
Thank you.

03:11.950 --> 03:13.960
Not both of them.
They're... They're... They're gonna...

03:13.970 --> 03:15.950
- Dear God, not both my babies.
- They're gonna find them, Kar.

03:15.960 --> 03:18.840
What's going on?
Grace is over there, looking for answers.

03:18.850 --> 03:20.830
Maybe your badge will help.

03:20.850 --> 03:21.970
Our Father who art in heaven.

03:21.980 --> 03:23.880
Hallowed be thy name.

03:23.890 --> 03:25.810
Thy Kingdom come,
thy will be done...

03:25.820 --> 03:27.840
There's a search operation in progress.

03:27.850 --> 03:29.960
Now, that's the official answer.
Tell us what's really going on.

03:29.970 --> 03:32.840
That's all the information
I have at this time.

03:32.850 --> 03:34.920
We're doing all we can.
But what are you doing?

03:34.930 --> 03:36.840
Who's looking for my family?

03:36.850 --> 03:37.960
Ma'am, y-you need to calm down.

03:37.970 --> 03:39.960
The hell I do!
My family's on that plane.

03:39.970 --> 03:42.840
Olive shouldn't be hearing this.
Hey, O!

03:42.850 --> 03:44.970
How was Jamaica?
Come tell Auntie...

03:44.980 --> 03:47.810
Oh, my God.
I should have said no.

03:47.820 --> 03:48.920
I should have made him
stay on our flight.

03:48.930 --> 03:50.920
We'd all be together now.
Cal would be here now.

03:50.930 --> 03:52.870
I thought you said
they were bumped.

03:52.890 --> 03:57.790
No, they volunteered for $400,
and now my son is missing.

03:57.810 --> 03:59.860
Oh, my God.
S-She didn't want to come back?

03:59.870 --> 04:01.830
I want my dad!

04:01.850 --> 04:03.850
I want my dad!
I know.

